      "content": "## 2) SAR REASONING (why these features matter for hERG)\nhERG blockers commonly have:\n1) **A protonatable basic nitrogen** \u2192 forms strong electrostatic interaction with the channel cavity (notably near residues such as **Tyr652/Phe656 region** via cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic contributions depending on pose).\n2) **Large aromatic/hydrophobic surfaces** \u2192 engage **\u03c0\u2013\u03c0 and hydrophobic interactions** with aromatic residues lining the pore (classically **Tyr652, Phe656** in hERG S6).\n3) **Appropriate spacing and flexibility** \u2192 allows the cationic center to sit in the cavity while aromatics occupy hydrophobic pockets.",
